I am confused with cpc cost and ad cost as it keeps changing without any justification

I understand how that can be confusing! The CPC (Cost Per Click) and overall ad cost can vary due to several factors such as competition, targeting settings, and bidding strategies. Our platform supports daily budgets at the ad set level and total budgets at the ad set, campaign, and account levels. While our system aims to spend the specified amount, actual spending may vary slightly. For more details on how costs are calculated, you can check out this article: [NewsBreak Advertising Cost](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/17959734533005-NewsBreak-Advertising-Cost). If you have any specific questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!

I was charged 0.06 cent per cpc cost and I go 21 clicks at that value. Suddenly, the 21 clicks increased to 35 clicks and the cpc cost changed to 0.35 cent without putting into consideration the 0.06 cent per clicks. This is not acceptable

I'm sorry to hear about the unexpected changes in your CPC cost. It sounds like there might be an issue with how the costs are being calculated or displayed. I recommend reaching out to our support team at adsupport@newsbreak.com with details of your campaign and billing concerns. They can investigate the issue and provide a resolution. Please allow 2-3 days for them to look into it.
